#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Saraṇānivagga "
msgstr "3. About Sarakāni "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 25. Dutiyasaraṇānisakkasutta → dutiyasarakānisuttaṃ (bj) | sarakāni or saraṇāni 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Dutiyasaraṇānisakkasutta "
msgstr "25. About Sarakāni the Sakyan (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.378, sc1
msgctxt "sn55.25:1.1"
msgid "Kapilavatthunidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Kapilavatthu. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena saraṇāni sakko kālaṅkato hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Sarakāni the Sakyan had passed away. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.3"
msgid "So bhagavatā byākato: "
msgstr "The Buddha declared that he was "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.4"
msgid "“sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti. "
msgstr "a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:1.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ sambahulā sakkā saṅgamma samāgamma ujjhāyanti khīyanti vipācenti: "
msgstr "At that, several Sakyans came together complaining, grumbling, and objecting, "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.6"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.7"
msgid "Ettha dāni ko na sotāpanno bhavissati. "
msgstr "Who can’t become a stream-enterer these days? "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.8"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma saraṇāni sakko kālaṅkato. "
msgstr "For the Buddha even declared Sarakāni to be a stream-enterer after he passed away. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.9"
msgid "So bhagavatā byākato: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.10"
msgid "‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:1.11"
msgid "Saraṇāni sakko sikkhāya aparipūrakārī ahosī”ti. "
msgstr "Sarakāni didn’t fulfill the training.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Mahānāma the Sakyan went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.25:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhante, saraṇāni sakko kālaṅkato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.2"
msgid "So bhagavatā byākato: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.3"
msgid "‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.4"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhante, sambahulā sakkā saṅgamma samāgamma ujjhāyanti khīyanti vipācenti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.5"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.6"
msgid "Ettha dāni ko na sotāpanno bhavissati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.7"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma saraṇāni sakko kālaṅkato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.8"
msgid "So bhagavatā byākato—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.9"
msgid "sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:2.10"
msgid "Saraṇāni sakko sikkhāya aparipūrakārī ahosī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.25:3.1"
msgid "“Yo so, mahānāma, dīgharattaṃ upāsako buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, so kathaṃ vinipātaṃ gaccheyya. "
msgstr "“Mahānāma, when a lay follower has for a long time gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, how could they go to the underworld? "

msgctxt "sn55.25:3.2"
msgid "Yañhi taṃ, mahānāma, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And if anyone should rightly be said to "

msgctxt "sn55.25:3.3"
msgid "‘dīgharattaṃ upāsako buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato’, saraṇāniṃ sakkaṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "have for a long time gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, it’s Sarakāni the Sakyan. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:3.4"
msgid "Saraṇāni, mahānāma, sakko dīgharattaṃ upāsako buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, so kathaṃ vinipātaṃ gaccheyya. "
msgstr "Sarakāni the Sakyan has for a long time gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.25:4.1"
msgid "Idha, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno—"
msgstr "Take a certain person who is sure and devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.2"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.3"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.4"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.5"
msgid "hāsapañño javanapañño vimuttiyā ca samannāgato. "
msgstr "They have laughing wisdom and swift wisdom, and are endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.6"
msgid "So āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:4.7"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo parimutto nirayā parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. "
msgstr "This person is exempt from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.25:5.1"
msgid "Idha pana, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno—"
msgstr "Take another person who is sure and devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.2"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.3"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.4"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.5"
msgid "hāsapañño javanapañño na ca vimuttiyā samannāgato. "
msgstr "They have laughing wisdom and swift wisdom, and are endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.6"
msgid "So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā antarāparinibbāyī hoti, upahaccaparinibbāyī hoti, asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti, sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti, uddhaṃsoto hoti akaniṭṭhagāmī. "
msgstr "With the ending of the five lower fetters, they’re extinguished between one life and the next … they’re extinguished upon landing … they’re extinguished without extra effort … they’re extinguished with extra effort … they head upstream, going to the Akaniṭṭha realm. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:5.7"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo parimutto nirayā parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. "
msgstr "This person, too, is exempt from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.379, sc6
msgctxt "sn55.25:6.1"
msgid "Idha pana, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno—"
msgstr "Take another person who is sure and devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.2"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.3"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.4"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.5"
msgid "na hāsapañño na javanapañño na ca vimuttiyā samannāgato. "
msgstr "But they don’t have laughing wisdom or swift wisdom, nor are they endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.6"
msgid "So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "With the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, they’re a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:6.7"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo parimutto nirayā parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. "
msgstr "This person, too, is exempt from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.25:7.1"
msgid "Idha pana, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno—"
msgstr "Take another person who is sure and devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.2"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.3"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.4"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.5"
msgid "na hāsapañño na javanapañño na ca vimuttiyā samannāgato. "
msgstr "But they don’t have laughing wisdom or swift wisdom, nor are they endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.6"
msgid "So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "With the ending of three fetters they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:7.7"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo parimutto nirayā parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. "
msgstr "This person, too, is exempt from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn55.25:8.1"
msgid "Idha pana, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo na heva kho buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno … pe … "
msgstr "Take another person who isn’t sure or devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.2"
msgid "na dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.3"
msgid "na saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.4"
msgid "na hāsapañño na javanapañño na ca vimuttiyā samannāgato; "
msgstr "They don’t have laughing wisdom or swift wisdom, nor are they endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.5"
msgid "api cassa ime dhammā honti—"
msgstr "Still, they have these qualities: "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.6"
msgid "saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.7"
msgid "Tathāgatappaveditā cassa dhammā paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti. "
msgstr "And they accept the principles proclaimed by the Realized One after considering them with a degree of wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:8.8"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo agantā nirayaṃ agantā tiracchānayoniṃ agantā pettivisayaṃ agantā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ. "
msgstr "This person, too, doesn’t go to hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They don’t go to places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn55.25:9.1"
msgid "Idha pana, mahānāma, ekacco puggalo na heva kho buddhe ekantagato hoti abhippasanno … "
msgstr "Take another person who isn’t sure or devoted to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.2"
msgid "na dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.3"
msgid "na saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.4"
msgid "na hāsapañño na javanapañño na ca vimuttiyā samannāgato; "
msgstr "They don’t have laughing wisdom or swift wisdom, nor are they endowed with freedom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.5"
msgid "api cassa ime dhammā honti—"
msgstr "Still, they have these qualities: "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.6"
msgid "saddhindriyaṃ … pe … paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.7"
msgid "Tathāgate cassa saddhāmattaṃ hoti pemamattaṃ. "
msgstr "And they have a degree of faith and love for the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:9.8"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahānāma, puggalo agantā nirayaṃ agantā tiracchānayoniṃ agantā pettivisayaṃ agantā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ. "
msgstr "This person, too, doesn’t go to hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They don’t go to places of loss, bad places, the underworld. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.380, sc10
#. VAR: dubbhūmaṃ → dubbhūmiṃ (bj, s1-3) | dubbhūmi (pts1)
#. VAR: asukhasayitāni → asukhāpassayitāni (mr)
#. VAR: ca na sammā → devo pana sammā (s1-3, km) | devo na sammā (mr)
msgctxt "sn55.25:10.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahānāma, dukkhettaṃ dubbhūmaṃ avihatakhāṇukaṃ, bījāni cassu khaṇḍāni pūtīni vātātapahatāni asārādāni asukhasayitāni, devo ca na sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a barren field, a barren ground, with uncleared stumps. And you had seeds that were broken, spoiled, weather-damaged, infertile, and ill kept. And the heavens didn’t provide enough rain. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:10.2"
msgid "Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyun”ti? "
msgstr "Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:10.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: durakkhāto → durākkhāto (s1-3) | dvākkhāto (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn55.25:10.4"
msgid "“Evameva kho, mahānāma, idha dhammo durakkhāto hoti duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito—"
msgstr "“In the same way, take a teaching that’s badly explained and badly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:10.5"
msgid "idamahaṃ dukkhettasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what I call a barren field. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:10.6"
msgid "Tasmiñca dhamme sāvako viharati dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī—"
msgstr "A disciple remains in such a teaching, practicing in line with that teaching, practicing it properly, living in line with that teaching. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:10.7"
msgid "idamahaṃ dubbījasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what I call a bad seed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: sukhettaṃ → sukkhettaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: devo cassa (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn55.25:11.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahānāma, sukhettaṃ subhūmaṃ suvihatakhāṇukaṃ, bījāni cassu akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sārādāni sukhasayitāni; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a fertile field, a fertile ground, well-cleared of stumps. And you had seeds that were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and well-kept. And there’s plenty of rainfall. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.2"
msgid "devo ca sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.3"
msgid "Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyun”ti? "
msgstr "Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:11.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.25:11.5"
msgid "“Evameva kho, mahānāma, idha dhammo svākkhāto hoti suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito—"
msgstr "“In the same way, take a teaching that’s well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.6"
msgid "idamahaṃ sukhettasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what I call a fertile field. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.7"
msgid "Tasmiñca dhamme sāvako viharati dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī—"
msgstr "A disciple remains in such a teaching, practicing in line with that teaching, practicing it properly, living in line with that teaching. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.8"
msgid "idamahaṃ subījasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what I call a good seed. "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.9"
msgid "Kimaṅgaṃ pana saraṇāniṃ sakkaṃ. "
msgstr "Why can’t this apply to Sarakāni? "

msgctxt "sn55.25:11.10"
msgid "Saraṇāni, mahānāma, sakko maraṇakāle sikkhāya paripūrakārī ahosī”ti. "
msgstr "Mahānāma, Sarakāni the Sakyan fulfilled the training at the time of his death.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.25:11.11"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

